{"title_page": "Bearsville Studios", "text_new": "'''Bearsville Studios''' was a [[recording studio]] in [[Bearsville, New York|Bearsville]], located just west of [[Woodstock, New York]], United States. The [[Bearsville Records]] label was under the same ownership.\n\n==History==\nThe studio was opened in 1969 by [[Albert Grossman]], manager of [[Bob Dylan]], [[The Band]], [[Janis Joplin]] and [[Todd Rundgren]]. Grossman served as the director until his death in 1986, after which time directorship was assumed by his wife, [[Sally Grossman]].\n\nThe studio did a great deal of demo work, and very little commercial advertising work, catering to its star-powered pedigree. The two-hour drive from [[New York City]], a \"retreat\" for some artists, combined with residences owned by Albert Grossman, amplified this value.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bearsville Studios, Speare Road, Bearsville, New York|url=http://jerrygarciasbrokendownpalaces.blogspot.com/2012/11/bearsville-studios-speare-road.html|website=jerrygarciasbrokendownpalaces.blogspot.com|publisher=Blogger|accessdate=30 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[The Replacements (band)|The Replacements]] had recording sessions at Bearsville for their ''[[Don't Tell a Soul]]'' album but the recordings were not used for the album. They were eventually released as part of the ''[[Dead Man's Pop]]'' box set in 2019. During the Bearsville recording session, the band trashed the recording studio and living quarters and played a game they called \"Dodge knife\" that was like [[dodgeball]] but using [[knife|knive]].<ref name=\"Rhino\">{{cite web |url=https://dangerousminds.net/comments/the_replacements_battle_their_producer_in_stormy_first_attempt_to_record_do |title=THE REPLACEMENTS BATTLE THEIR PRODUCER IN STORMY FIRST ATTEMPT TO RECORD \u2018DON\u2019T TELL A SOUL\u2019 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2019-09-26 |website=dangerousminds.net |access-date=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090630003629/http://www.bearsvillestudios.com/ Bearsville Studios website]\n\n\n{{Coord|42|2|38|N|74|8|42|W|display=title}}\n[[Category:Recording studios in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Media in Ulster County, New York]]\n[[Category:Woodstock, New York]]\n[[Category:Entertainment companies established in 1969]]\n[[Category:Companies disestablished in 2004]]\n[[Category:1969 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:2004 disestablishments in New York (state)]]\n", "text_old": "'''Bearsville Studios''' was a [[recording studio]] in [[Bearsville, New York|Bearsville]], located just west of [[Woodstock, New York]], United States. The [[Bearsville Records]] label was under the same ownership.\n\n==History==\nThe studio was opened in 1969 by [[Albert Grossman]], manager of [[Bob Dylan]], [[The Band]], [[Janis Joplin]] and [[Todd Rundgren]]. Grossman served as the director until his death in 1986, after which time directorship was assumed by his wife, [[Sally Grossman]].\n\nThe studio did a great deal of demo work, and very little commercial advertising work, catering to its star-powered pedigree. The two-hour drive from [[New York City]], a \"retreat\" for some artists, combined with residences owned by Albert Grossman, amplified this value.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bearsville Studios, Speare Road, Bearsville, New York|url=http://jerrygarciasbrokendownpalaces.blogspot.com/2012/11/bearsville-studios-speare-road.html|website=jerrygarciasbrokendownpalaces.blogspot.com|publisher=Blogger|accessdate=30 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[The Replacements (band)|The Replacements]] had recording sessions at Bearsville for their [[Don't Tell a Soul]] album but the recordings were not used for the album. They were eventually released as part of the [[Dead Man's Pop]] box set in 2019. During the Bearsville recording session, the band trashed the recording studio and living quarters and played a game they called \"Dodge knife\" that was like [[dodgeball]] but using [[knife|knive]].<ref name=\"Rhino\">{{cite web |url=https://dangerousminds.net/comments/the_replacements_battle_their_producer_in_stormy_first_attempt_to_record_do |title=THE REPLACEMENTS BATTLE THEIR PRODUCER IN STORMY FIRST ATTEMPT TO RECORD \u2018DON\u2019T TELL A SOUL\u2019 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2019-09-26 |website=dangerousminds.net |access-date=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090630003629/http://www.bearsvillestudios.com/ Bearsville Studios website]\n\n\n{{Coord|42|2|38|N|74|8|42|W|display=title}}\n[[Category:Recording studios in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Media in Ulster County, New York]]\n[[Category:Woodstock, New York]]\n[[Category:Entertainment companies established in 1969]]\n[[Category:Companies disestablished in 2004]]\n[[Category:1969 establishments in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:2004 disestablishments in New York (state)]]\n", "name_user": "Airproofing", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory:added italics", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bearsville_Studios"}
